3 Section 2. R.S. 48:255.9 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
4 §255.9. Average bid method; authority
5 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, a pilot
6 program is hereby established to authorize the department and the office of
7 Louisiana highway construction to use the average bid method to determine the
8 bidder to whom a contract for public works shall be awarded. The pilot
9 program shall be limited to four state funded projects per year, two each for the
10 department and the office of Louisiana highway construction, and subject to the
11 approval of the Senate and House committees on transportation, highways and
12 public works.
13 B.(1) For purposes of this Section, if five or more responsive bids are
14 received, the department shall average the bids, excluding the highest and
15 lowest responsive bids. The department shall award the contract to the bidder
16 whose responsive bid is closest to the average. If two or more bids are equally
17 close, award shall be made to the lower bid. If no bid is equal to or less than the
18 average mean, award shall be made to the lowest responsible bidder.
19 (2) If less than three responsive bids are received, all bids will be
20 rejected.
21 C. The provisions of this Section shall not apply to professional services.
22 Section 3. The provisions of this Section shall terminate March 1, 2028 unless
23 legislatively extended.
