SB NO. 513
Proposed law authorizes DOTD and OLHC to use the average bid method as part of a pilot
program with four state funded projects per year, two each for the department and the office
of Louisiana highway construction. Proposed law further provides the projects are subject
to the approval of the Senate and House committees on transportation, highways and public
works.
Proposed law provides when five or more responsive bids are received, the average of the
bids, excluding the highest and lowest responsive bids will be awarded to the bidder whose
responsive bid is closest to the average. Proposed law further provides when two or more
bids are equally close, award will be made to the lower bid. Proposed law further provides
when less than three responsive bids are received, all bids will be rejected.
Proposed law does not apply to professional services.
Proposed law provides for a sunset date of March 1, 2028.
Effective August 1, 2026
(Amends R.S. 38:2225.2.6(A); adds R.S. 48:255.9)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by Senate
Senate Floor Amendments to engrossed bill
1. Removes pilot program authorizing fifteen projects per year, subject to the
approval of the Senate and House committees on transportation, highways
and public works, for local governmental subdivisions or political
subdivisions to use the average bid method.
2. Removes definitions.
3. Removes specifications and requirements for local governmental
subdivisions and political subdivisions relative to bidding documents and
notification to Senate and House committees on transportation, highways and
public works.
5. Adds ability for airports to use design build method of delivery.
6. Adds provision for DOTD and OLHC to use average bid method as part of
pilot program.
7. Adds sunset date.
